The Top Employers Institute has released its the ranking of the top employers in South Africa for 2020. The ranking recognises top employers based on a global 4-stage programme governed by a strict standardised process which includes a rigorous validation & audit of each organisation. A record 230 organisations officially registered to participate in this year’s programme, 210 organisations spanning 32 African countries and 23 industry sectors were certified. Billy Elliott, Top Employers Institute regional manager for Africa, said that the certification provides employers with an important quality metric that enables them to position their brands more effectively in the attraction, retention, and engagement of top talent. “The Top Employers Institute is not just about certifying Africa’s Top Employers. We have seen a progression of HR in Africa over the last few years, and it is our role to empower and advance people strategies across the world. We are driven not just to certify but to benchmark and connect outstanding employers around the world,” he said. The institute ranked the best companies to work for by industry as outlined below. Mercedes-Benz South Africa – Automotive <img class="aligncenter wp-image-222391 size-full" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Mercedes-e1517406663737.jpeg" alt="" width="640" height="427" /> Sasol Limited – Chemicals & Energy <img class="size-full wp-image-217749 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2018/01/Sasol-e1515047779480.jpg" alt="" width="640" height="427" /> Hilti (South Africa)  – Construction Services <img class="size-full wp-image-356857 aligncenter" src="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Hilti.png" alt="" width="640" height="430" srcset="https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Hilti.png 640w, https://businesstech.co.za/news/wp-content/uploads/2019/11/Hilti-300x202.png 300w" sizes="(max-width: 709px) 85vw, (max-width: